| ATM Turns 40                                                       |
|   from the atm-fees-are-such-a-scam dept.                          |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Monday June 25, @08:43 (The Almighty Buck) |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/25/1215239              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]01100111 writes "[1]The world's first ATM was installed in a branch of
Barclays in Enfield, north London, 40 years ago this week. Inspiration
had struck Mr Shepherd-Barron, now 82, while he was in the bath. The
machine paid out a maximum of £10 a time." It struck me there must be a
way I could get my own money, anywhere in the world or the UK. I hit upon
the idea of a chocolate bar dispenser, but replacing chocolate with
cash.""

