| Mono Coders Hack Linux Silverlight in 21 Days                      |
|   from the break-out-the-red-bull-and-go-go-go dept.               |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Monday June 25, @11:55 (Novell)            |
|   http://developers.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/25/1427225   |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Etrigoth writes "After the recent announcement of Silverlight by
Microsoft at their Mix event in Vegas, [0]Miguel de Icaza galvanised his
team of developers in the Mono group at [1]Novell to create a Linux
implementation, a so-called 'Moonlight'. Remarkably, they achieved this
in [2]21 Days. Although they were first introduced to Silverlight at the
Las Vegas Mix, de Icaza was invited by a representative of Microsoft
France for a 10 minute demonstration at the Paris Re-Mix 07 keynote
conference, should they have anything to show.
Joshua, a blogger for Microsoft has confirmed that the Mono team [3]did
not know anything about Silverlight 1.1 before its launch. Other members
of this team have blogged about this incredible achievement, [4]Moonlight
hack-a-thon. It's worth noting from a developer perspective that
Moonlight is not Mono and [5]doesn't require Mono to work"

Discuss this story at:
    http://developers.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/25/1427225

