[0]Raver32 writes to tell us the X Prize Foundation has announced
[1]eight of the nine groups planning to compete in this year's Northrop
Grumman Lunar Lander Challenge. "The ninth team requested to remain
confidential, lending an air of controversy to the announcement. Space
bloggers have surmised the ninth team is Amazon.com founder Jeff Bezos'
Blue Origin, but sources told SPACE.com that information was wrong. Their
confidentiality period ends 60 days before the start of the competition
at which time the X Prize Foundation will announce the team's name."

