+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

teh_commodore writes to tell us that Breitbart has a look at how
[0]Citizen Journalism is shining a whole new light on China. "Recognizing
the threat of China's growing online community, Chinese President Hu
Jintao called in January for the Internet to be 'purified', and the
government has since launched a number of online crackdowns. [...] 'One
cannot truly say that the Internet in China is becoming more and more
free, because at the same time as the development of citizen journalists,
the government finds ways of blocking or censoring content,' Pain said."

