| The British Steam Car Challenge                                    |
|   from the dr.-stanley-i-presume dept.                             |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday June 25, @19:19 (Power)              |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/25/2243241     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Van Cutter Romney sends us word of a [1]British steam-powered car that
will attempt to set a world record speed of 200 mph. The car, constructed
on a tubular chassis, holds four boilers that deliver four megawatts of
power, producing 300 bhp. The current record of 127.659 mph was
established in 1906. [2]More photos and specs at the Steam Car Club of
Great Britain's site.

